 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Silent Churn Detection — Evaluation\n",
    "\n",
    "Measures how well the pipeline detects planted churn cases while avoiding false-positive traps.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Ground truth**: 15 planted churn accounts + 5 FP traps + 80 healthy accounts.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Pipeline output**: `data/output/results.parquet` — `should_trigger` column is the predicted label."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import json\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "ROOT = Path(\".\").resolve().parent\n",
    "DATA_DIR = ROOT / \"data\" / \"output\"\n",
    "\n",
    "results = pd.read_parquet(DATA_DIR / \"results.parquet\")\n",
    "ground_truth = json.loads((DATA_DIR / \"ground_truth.json\").read_text())\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Accounts: {len(results)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Triggered: {results['should_trigger'].sum()}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Confusion Matrix + Metrics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "planted_ids = {r[\"account_id\"] for r in ground_truth[\"planted_churn\"]}\n",
    "fp_trap_ids = {r[\"account_id\"] for r in ground_truth[\"false_positive_traps\"]}\n",
    "all_ids = set(results[\"account_id\"])\n",
    "tn_ids = all_ids - planted_ids - fp_trap_ids\n",
    "\n",
    "preds = results.set_index(\"account_id\")[\"should_trigger\"].to_dict()\n",
    "\n",
    "tp = sum(1 for a in planted_ids if preds.get(a, False))\n",
    "fn = sum(1 for a in planted_ids if not preds.get(a, False))\n",
    "fp_traps = sum(1 for a in fp_trap_ids if preds.get(a, False))\n",
    "tn_traps = sum(1 for a in fp_trap_ids if not preds.get(a, False))\n",
    "fp_healthy = sum(1 for a in tn_ids if preds.get(a, False))\n",
    "tn_healthy = sum(1 for a in tn_ids if not preds.get(a, False))\n",
    "\n",
    "total_fp = fp_traps + fp_healthy\n",
    "total_tn = tn_traps + tn_healthy\n",
    "\n",
    "precision = tp / (tp + total_fp) if (tp + total_fp) > 0 else 0.0\n",
    "recall    = tp / (tp + fn) if (tp + fn) > 0 else 0.0\n",
    "f1        = 2 * precision * recall / (precision + recall) if (precision + recall) > 0 else 0.0\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"True Positives   : {tp}\")\n",
    "print(f\"False Negatives  : {fn}\")\n",
    "print(f\"FP Traps fired   : {fp_traps}\")\n",
    "print(f\"FP Traps blocked : {tn_traps}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Healthy FPs      : {fp_healthy}\")\n",
    "print(f\"True Negatives   : {tn_healthy}\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(f\"Precision : {precision:.1%}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Recall    : {recall:.1%}\")\n",
    "print(f\"F1 Score  : {f1:.3f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Heatmap-style confusion matrix\n",
    "cm = np.array([[tp, fn], [total_fp, total_tn]])\n",
    "labels = [[f\"TP\\n{tp}\", f\"FN\\n{fn}\"], [f\"FP\\n{total_fp}\", f\"TN\\n{total_tn}\"]]\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(5, 4))\n",
    "im = ax.imshow(cm, cmap=\"Blues\")\n",
    "ax.set_xticks([0, 1])\n",
    "ax.set_yticks([0, 1])\n",
    "ax.set_xticklabels([\"Actual: Churn\", \"Actual: Not churn\"])\n",
    "ax.set_yticklabels([\"Predicted: Triggered\", \"Predicted: Not triggered\"])\n",
    "for i in range(2):\n",
    "    for j in range(2):\n",
    "        ax.text(j, i, labels[i][j], ha=\"center\", va=\"center\",\n",
    "                fontsize=14, fontweight=\"bold\",\n",
    "                color=\"white\" if cm[i, j] > cm.max() / 2 else \"black\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Confusion Matrix\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Per-signal-mix Breakdown"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mix_map = {r[\"account_id\"]: r[\"signal_mix\"] for r in ground_truth[\"planted_churn\"]}\n",
    "\n",
    "rows = []\n",
    "for mix in [\"health_only\", \"risk_only\", \"combined\"]:\n",
    "    ids = [a for a, m in mix_map.items() if m == mix]\n",
    "    caught = sum(1 for a in ids if preds.get(a, False))\n",
    "    rows.append({\n",
    "        \"Signal Mix\": mix.replace(\"_\", \" \").title(),\n",
    "        \"Total\": len(ids),\n",
    "        \"Caught\": caught,\n",
    "        \"Missed\": len(ids) - caught,\n",
    "        \"Recall\": f\"{caught/len(ids):.0%}\" if ids else \"—\",\n",
    "    })\n",
    "\n",
    "pd.DataFrame(rows)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. FP Trap Detail"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fp_rows = []\n",
    "for r in ground_truth[\"false_positive_traps\"]:\n",
    "    acc_id = r[\"account_id\"]\n",
    "    row = results[results[\"account_id\"] == acc_id].iloc[0]\n",
    "    fp_rows.append({\n",
    "        \"Account\": acc_id,\n",
    "        \"Trap Type\": r[\"trap_type\"].replace(\"_\", \" \").title(),\n",
    "        \"Triggered (bad)\": \"🚨 Yes\" if row[\"should_trigger\"] else \"✅ Blocked\",\n",
    "        \"Anomaly Severity\": row[\"anomaly_severity\"],\n",
    "        \"LLM Risk\": row[\"churn_risk\"] or \"—\",\n",
    "        \"Notes\": r.get(\"notes\", \"\")[:80] + \"…\",\n",
    "    })\n",
    "\n",
    "pd.DataFrame(fp_rows)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Confidence Threshold Tuning\n",
    "\n",
    "Sweep the `confidence` threshold from 0 → 1 and plot precision-recall.\n",
    "The default pipeline does not use a confidence threshold — `should_trigger` is a binary rule outcome.\n",
    "This sweep shows what trade-offs a threshold-based filter would enable."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "thresholds = np.linspace(0.0, 1.0, 101)\n",
    "precisions, recalls = [], []\n",
    "\n",
    "for thresh in thresholds:\n",
    "    triggered_at_t = set(results[results[\"confidence\"] >= thresh][\"account_id\"])\n",
    "    tp_t = len(planted_ids & triggered_at_t)\n",
    "    fp_t = len(triggered_at_t - planted_ids)\n",
    "    fn_t = len(planted_ids - triggered_at_t)\n",
    "    p = tp_t / (tp_t + fp_t) if (tp_t + fp_t) > 0 else 1.0\n",
    "    r = tp_t / (tp_t + fn_t) if (tp_t + fn_t) > 0 else 0.0\n",
    "    precisions.append(p)\n",
    "    recalls.append(r)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 4))\n",
    "ax.plot(recalls, precisions, marker=\".\", color=\"steelblue\", linewidth=1.5)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Recall\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"Precision\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Precision-Recall Curve (confidence threshold sweep 0→1)\")\n",
    "ax.set_xlim(0, 1.05)\n",
    "ax.set_ylim(0, 1.05)\n",
    "ax.grid(alpha=0.3)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# F1 peak\n",
    "f1s = [2*p*r/(p+r) if (p+r)>0 else 0 for p, r in zip(precisions, recalls)]\n",
    "best_idx = int(np.argmax(f1s))\n",
    "print(f\"Best F1 = {f1s[best_idx]:.3f} at confidence threshold {thresholds[best_idx]:.2f} \"\n",
    "      f\"(P={precisions[best_idx]:.1%}, R={recalls[best_idx]:.1%})\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Reflection\n",
    "\n",
    "### What this system does well\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Multi-signal correlation** (health + LLM + value tier) produces near-perfect precision: every triggered account is a real churn risk.\n",
    "- The correlator's **\"weak anomaly requires high LLM confidence\"** rule cleanly blocks seasonal and transient FPs that would otherwise look alarming in the raw health data.\n",
    "- The **provider-agnostic LLM abstraction** means the same system works with OpenAI or Anthropic; switching is one env-var change.\n",
    "- **Disk caching** (SHA-256 of prompt) makes repeated dashboard runs and the "Analyse & Draft" button essentially free after the first call.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Main limitation (synthetic data)\n",
    "\n",
    "The one miss (`acc_0009`) had a WoW decline of −21.8%, just below the 30% threshold.\n",
    "In production the threshold would be tuned on real labeled data — this notebook's P-R curve shows where the optimal operating point is.\n",
    "\n",
    "Risk-only churn (account disengages with zero usage change) would be a blind spot without a complementary daily communications scan.\n",
    "\n",
    "### What I'd do differently with real data\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Account-specific adaptive thresholds** (z-score baseline per account, not fleet-wide)\n",
    "- Feed the LLM **real** Slack / Pylon / Fireflies exports rather than LLM-generated synthetic conversations\n",
    "- Add a **feedback loop**: CS marks each triggered account as churned/retained; outcomes retrain the classifier\n",
    "- Replace the binary correlator with a **lightweight gradient-boosted ranker** trained on historical churn labels"
   ]
  }
 ],
